company_description:
A career in home health care is a rewarding path, allowing you to make a real difference in people’s lives every day. When you pursue a career with BAYADA, you join a nationally respected team that has been a leader in providing quality care and support inside the home since 1975.

As a BAYADA professional, you will take advantage of support, resources, and supervision to help you develop and grow your leadership potential. From your first day of orientation through ongoing training in best practices, new protocols, state-of-the-art technologies, safety, and communication, BAYADA will nurture your success and create opportunities for you to achieve your career goals.

We employ nearly 23,000 full-time and part-time clinical and non-clinical professionals. Choosing a career path with BAYADA will allow you to develop and use your skills in any one of our specialty practices, including, adult nursing, assistive care, pediatrics, habilitation, home health, or hospice. If you share our commitment to delivering the highest quality care and keeping clients safe at home, then join our team of compassionate professionals.

Check out our jobs: https://www.giftedhealthcare.com/jobs/

Learn about us: https://www.linkedin.com/company/gifted-healthcare

See what people think: Working at Gifted Healthcare - Glassdoor

custom_email_body:
I'm Bayada's first Career Navigator!  My job is to help find you a career with Bayada that you can be passionate about!  I have several opportunities in your area for management, hourly shift care, visits, and per diem!

Our nurses choose their own hours, locations, and clients. Whether it be full-time, part-time, per diem, weekends, or last minute call-outs, we have a shift to meet your scheduling needs. Because we provide care for such a wide range of clients, we make every effort for our staff to select assignments that match their expertise and preference. 

Please connect with me at your earliest convenience to learn more about our exciting opportunities. If you are not interested at this time, please known I am here to help for future consideration.

I look forward to working with you!

-----------------------

Kara Lloyd

Sourcing Manager (RPO) | BAYADA Home Health Care

4300 Haddonfield Road, East Building. Pennsauken, NJ  08109

O: 856-406-0164| M: 267-453-8888 |  Cisco Ext.: 0198-19 | bayada.com

 

Love what you do? Spread the love by referring a friend through BAYADA's Talent Scout bonus program. Click here: http://bhhc.co/talentbonus
